{
  "local_port": 57130,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I keep getting dock connected on my Android, how do I get it off?",
  "response": "The \"dock connected\" notification on Android typically appears when your device is connected to a dock or a similar accessory. If you're not using a dock and want to get rid of this notification, here are some steps you can try:\n\n1. **Check Physical Connections:**\n   - Ensure your device is not physically connected to any dock or similar accessory. Sometimes, the notification can appear due to a loose or faulty connection.\n\n2. **Restart Your Device:**\n   - A simple restart can often resolve temporary software glitches. Turn off your device, wait a few seconds, and then turn it back on.\n\n3. **Check for Software Updates:**\n   - Go to **Settings > System > System update** and check if there are any updates available for your device. Updating to the latest software can fix known issues.\n\n4. **Disable Dock Notifications:**\n   - Some devices allow you to disable dock notifications. Go to **Settings > Apps & notifications > See all apps**, and look for \"Dock\" or a similar app. If you find it, you can clear its data or disable notifications.\n\n5. **Use Safe Mode:**\n   - Boot your device into Safe Mode to see if the issue persists. If the notification doesn\u2019t appear in Safe Mode, it might be caused by a third-party app.\n     - To enter Safe Mode, press and hold the power button until the power off menu appears. Then, press and hold \"Power off\" until you see the Safe Mode prompt. Tap \"OK\" to reboot into Safe Mode.\n\n6. **Clear Cache Partition:**\n   - Clearing the cache partition can sometimes resolve persistent notifications. The steps to do this vary by device but generally involve booting into recovery mode and selecting the option to clear the cache partition.\n\n7. **Factory Reset:**\n   - As a last resort, you can perform a factory reset. Be sure to back up your data first, as this will erase all data on your device.\n     - Go to **Settings > System > Reset options > Erase all data (factory reset)** and follow the prompts.\n\nIf none of these steps resolve the issue, it might be worth contacting the manufacturer's support or visiting a service center, as there could be a hardware issue with your device.",
